<TITLE> Banks give PM Tk 7cr for bereaved families </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 10 (bdnews24.com)  The private banks have given the prime minister Tk 7 crore in assistance for the families of the BDR officers slain in the Feb. 25-26 revolt in border guards' headquarters. A 28-strong delegation of the Bangladesh Association of Banks led by its president Exim Bank chairman Nazrul Islam Majumder met with Sheikh Hasina at her residence Tuesday morning and handed her the cheque. Finance minister AMA Muhith, commerce minister Faruq Khan and the prime minister's press secretary Abul Kalam Azad were present there. The press secretary said the BAB lauded the prime minister's efficient handling of the crisis and said her prompt intervention averted many more casualties. They assured Hasina that those family members of the slain army officers who were now eligible would be given jobs and banks would take care of the study costs of the children. Majumder told bdnews24.com each bank contributed Tk 25 lakh to the fund.
